title: Do face masks really make us look more attractive?
description:
Have you ever been disappointed when a person who looked attractive took off their face mask?
A big realisation everyone seemed to have stumbled upon during the pandemic was that people looked more attractive when they are wearing face masks. This idea got so big in the internet that it even sparked a "mask fishing" trend on TikTok in 2021. 

Do face masks really make us look more attractive?

Quick answer: Yes, it does.

According to a new study conducted by researchers in Philadelphia, people who wear face masks were rated as being more attractive than those who werenâ€™t wearing a face mask.

The study was conducted online, where 60 faces were rated with and without a mask from which a total of 496  participant responses were analysed. 

Interestingly, the largest percentage improvements were seen in the unattractive groups, with an approximately 42% increase in ratings for both women and men after they put on a face mask.

This arises because people fill in the missing parts with their positive expectations.
So, your mind will automatically imagine an attractive face beneath the mask that you canâ€™t see under.
Furthermore, in other mask-related studies conducted in Japan, it was shown that those wearing masks were perceived to be healthier than those not wearing masks after the eruption of the COVID-19 pandemic compared to pre-pandemic times. 

Lastly, there was also a survey which found that 88 percent of adult women in the U.S. perceived men who wore a face mask in public during the COVID-19 pandemic to be sexier than those who did not.

So, you can now be sure that wearing a mask will make you look more attractive to others.

In addition, there is another advantage of wearing a mask.
You don't have to make contact with the people you don't like!

title: When you're hotter with a mask on...
description:
Ever since Covid, I felt like I was receiving more smiles from strangers than I normally do. That felt pretty good. Well, not for too long. I ask way too many questions. Studies found that in general, when a part of a face is hidden from us, our brain has the tendency to imagine the whole thing to be more attractive than it really is. So there really isn't a choice. We are all mask fishing. Let's not be blaming one or the other or putting them down, it's our own bias in our head. 

So now you know I'll still be rocking a mask in 2050. 

And this is in general- people do differ in whether they're more attractive in their eyes and brows area or in their jaw area- we are all beautiful, my people. 

_______________________________________________________________________________
ğŸ§  this BRAIN TALKS!!! ğŸ§ 

I invented a machine that takes me inside of my head and get a look at my brain. 
... and THIS BRAIN TALKS! (Surprise surprise we all talk to ourselves) 

I took this opportunity to ask him of all the questions I had about myself and my inner workings. And I'm recording the conversations and sharing them on this channel for you guys. Did not really ask for his consent on this, but unlike me, he seems to be happy about being in the spotlight. Sometimes, he tires me out but he insists that I visit him once a while, quoting this- "Know Thyself" quote, which I agree is important. 

So yeah, whatever he said: "Know Thyself". Come visit this channel often. 

If you have any suggestions or feedback, please let me know through the comments section. 
And I'd also love to hear any topic that you find fascinating or questions you'd like to ask the brain, and would want me to cover on this channel. I'll do it. 

New Videos Every 2 or 3 days

title: Why YOU Look Uglier Without A Mask

title: Glow up Tips for men 32/100 #shorts #glowup #glowuptips #summer
description:
In recent years, the term 'glow-up' has become increasingly popular, referring to the transformation of a person from an average-looking individual to someone who is confident, stylish, and attractive. Formerly associated with women, this term has gained traction amongst men, by challenging societal norms surrounding masculinity, fashion, and grooming.

In this YouTube short, we will explore some essential tips for men to get a glow-up. We will dive specifically into why sun protection is the root of every good skin routine and why every man should prioritize using SPF on a daily basis.

One of the primary reasons why SPF is crucial for a glow-up is that it helps to prevent sun damage. Sun damage can cause premature ageing, dark spots, and increases the risk of skin cancer. By applying sunscreen daily, you are blocking harmful UV rays from penetrating your skin and causing long-term damage to your skin.

Another reason why SPF is essential for a glow-up is that it helps to promote an even skin tone. Exposure to the sun can cause pigment changes in the skin, resulting in uneven skin tone and dark spots. Once these spots develop, they can be incredibly challenging to remove. By using SPF products, you can prevent the development of these spots, and maintain healthy, even skin over time.

Finally, sunscreen helps to create a barrier between your skin and environmental pollutants. Exposure to toxins in the environment, such as pollution, can cause the skin to become dry and dull. By using SPF products, you can protect your skin from environmental pollutants and keep it looking healthy and revitalized.

In conclusion, if you are a man looking to get a glow-up, then using SPF products daily should be at the top of your grooming routine. By using SPF, you are taking a crucial step in preventing sun damage, promoting an even skin tone, and protecting your skin from environmental pollutants. Remember, a good glow-up is all about looking and feeling confident, and with a little bit of effort, it's something that every man can achieve.

title: The Mistake Guys Make When Trying to Be More Handsome
description:
In this video, we will discuss the common mistake that guys make when trying to be more handsome. Many men fall into the trap of letting girls dictate the standards of handsomeness, seeking validation and compliments from others. This can lead to insecurity and a constant need for approval. 

The solution? Define what handsomeness means to you. Who is your ideal example of handsomeness? Use that as your standard, rather than constantly changing your appearance to fit someone else's preferences. Remember, men have their own unique taste and should prioritize their own definition of attractiveness. 

Don't fall into the trap of conforming to others' standards. Embrace your own definition of handsomeness and feel confident in your own skin. Watch this video to learn more about how to avoid this common mistake and define your own standard of handsomeness. 

Stay tuned for more tips on self-confidence and self-acceptance. Remember, true beauty comes from within.

After watching this video, take action by incorporating a self-care activity into your daily routine. Whether it's washing your face, exercising, meditating, or simply getting a good night's sleep, prioritize your self-care to unlock your true handsomeness potential.

title: Stoicism, Relationships, Female Attraction, Fragrances, Empathy, Body Language, Emotional Complexity
description:
Hello, welcome to our channel! Today we're going to dive into five essential lessons for understanding and strengthening your interpersonal relationships, especially when it comes to attracting and maintaining female interest.
In the first lesson, we will discuss the power of smell and fragrances. Did you know that choosing the right fragrance can significantly increase your chances of attraction? Women are highly sensitive to smells, and a well-made choice can make all the difference!
Next, we'll explore how availability and interest should be balanced. Men who are not very available from the beginning are more likely to attract female interest. Showing respect without appearing needy is the key to success.
Our third lesson covers pre-screening and attractiveness. Women tend to find men more attractive when they see that other women are interested in them. Making friends with women and being surrounded by them can naturally and genuinely increase your attractiveness.
In the fourth lesson, we will talk about the importance of body language and communication. Understanding and responding to female body language is crucial to creating and maintaining interest. Women use gestures and signals to show their interest and expect reciprocity. Not responding to these signals can lead to disinterest.
Finally, in the fifth lesson, we will discuss female emotional complexity. Women value understanding and empathy in relationships. Being attentive to your emotions and needs is essential to strengthening the connection and building a lasting relationship.

title: Dermatologist explains the rise of aesthetic procedures for men.
description:
Brotox and Beyond: The Rise of Aesthetic Procedures for Men
In recent years, the world of aesthetic enhancements has seen a significant shift. No longer just a domain for women, men are increasingly seeking cosmetic procedures to maintain a youthful and refreshed appearance. Among these, "Brotox" â€“ Botox for men â€“ has emerged as a popular choice. This trend reflects a broader acceptance of men's grooming and self-care, challenging traditional notions of masculinity.

Botox, a neurotoxin that reduces the appearance of wrinkles by relaxing facial muscles, offers men a way to combat the signs of aging without the need for invasive surgery. The results are subtle yet effective, making it an attractive option for those looking to enhance their natural features while maintaining a rugged, masculine look.

But Brotox is just the beginning. Men are also exploring other aesthetic treatments such as dermal fillers to restore volume, laser treatments for skin rejuvenation, and body contouring procedures to sculpt their physique. These treatments cater to a growing desire among men to look their best at any age, boosting confidence both personally and professionally.

The rise of male aesthetic procedures signals a shift in societal attitudes towards male beauty and self-care. It underscores a new era where men can freely pursue cosmetic enhancements without stigma, embracing the benefits of modern dermatology and cosmetic surgery. Whether it's to stay competitive in the workplace, feel more attractive, or simply boost self-esteem, men are taking charge of their appearance like never before.

This transformation in the cosmetic industry reflects a broader cultural change, where self-improvement and personal care are universally acknowledged and celebrated. As more men share their positive experiences, the trend is likely to continue growing, paving the way for future innovations and acceptance in male aesthetics.

So, here's to the modern man â€“ confident, self-assured, and unapologetically embracing the power of Brotox and beyond. #Brotox #Men'sAesthetics #SelfCare #ModernMasculinity #YouthfulLook #ConfidenceBoost

title: Asian Beauty products , Makeup Tutorial Cute Look, Skincare    Makeup Artists #shorts #makeup#beauty
description:
A "Cute Look" makeup tutorial typically aims for a fresh, youthful appearance that's both playful and polished. It usually involves a balance of dewy skin, soft colors, and subtle details. Here's a step-by-step guide to achieving this look:

### 1. **Skincare Prep**

**Cleanser**: Start with a gentle cleanser to ensure your skin is fresh and free of impurities.

**Toner**: Apply a toner to balance your skinâ€™s pH and tighten pores.

**Serum**: Use a hydrating serum to provide a glowing base.

**Moisturizer**: Apply a lightweight moisturizer to keep your skin plump and hydrated.

**Sunscreen**: Donâ€™t forget sunscreen for daily protection.

**Primer**: Use a primer to smooth the skinâ€™s surface and help makeup last longer.

### 2. **Base Makeup**

**Foundation**: Opt for a light to medium coverage foundation or a BB cream to even out your skin tone while keeping a natural finish. 

**Concealer**: Use concealer to brighten under the eyes and cover any blemishes or redness.

**Powder**: Lightly set your makeup with a translucent powder to avoid excess shine but maintain a dewy look.

**Blush**: Apply a soft, rosy blush to the apples of your cheeks for a youthful flush. Cream blushes work well for a natural look.

### 3. **Eyes**

**Eyebrows**: Fill in your eyebrows with a pencil or powder, keeping them soft and natural.

**Eyeshadow**: Use light, neutral shades for the eyes. Soft pinks, peaches, or light browns work well. Apply a shimmery shade on the lid for a touch of sparkle.

**Eyeliner**: A thin line of brown or black eyeliner along the upper lash line enhances the eyes without being too harsh. For a more playful look, you can use a pencil liner for a softer line.

**Mascara**: Apply a coat or two of mascara to your upper lashes for added definition. Use a waterproof formula if needed to prevent smudging.

**Highlighter**: Apply a highlighter to the high points of your face, like the cheekbones, bridge of the nose, and brow bone, for a dewy glow.

### 4. **Lips**

**Lip Balm**: Start with a hydrating lip balm to keep your lips soft.

**Lip Color**: Choose a sweet, flattering shade like pink or peach. Tinted lip balms or glosses offer a fresh, natural finish.

### 5. **Finishing Touches**

**Setting Spray**: Use a setting spray to lock in your makeup and give your skin a radiant finish.

This look emphasizes a healthy, glowing complexion and gentle colors to achieve a sweet and approachable vibe.

description:
About Professional Beauty India

Professional Beauty India organised by Ideas Exchange Pvt Ltd, a part of the global Professional Beauty group was brought from London, UK to Delhi, India in 2012 with its inaugural show bringing professional from various sectors of the beauty business closer, Professional Beauty India has grown to become the hotspot for business to business spectrum within the beauty and wellness industry.

Since its launch in India in 2012, Professional Beauty has successfully served the Northern market for nearly a decade. With the rise of West Indiaâ€™s beauty industry, Professional Beauty has shifted its base to Mumbai for the year 2013 which brings you an exciting new line-up of business opportunities with years passing and we kept on expanding to different markets.

From its modest launch, PBI has grown to be South Asia's leading B2B trade exhibition for the beauty, cosmetics and hair industry, an annual opportunity for industry professionals to connect, meet existing and new brands, distributors, salon and spa colleagues to understand the latest trends and challenges impacting the industry, and how to imbibe those trends to grow their businesses through our major shows in: Bangalore, Chennai, Delhi, Kolkata and Mumbai.

To date, Professional Beauty has brought over 200,000 trade buyers in contact with over 2000 brands making it the most successful beauty trade show in South Asia.

title: Daily Habits That Elevate Your Beauty! ğŸ’– #beautytips #beautiful
description:
Looking attractive isnâ€™t just about looks; itâ€™s about self-care, confidence, and glowing from within! âœ¨
From skincare routines to posture tips, these simple habits can transform your appearance and boost your confidence. Start practicing these today and watch yourself become the best version of YOU!

1 Healthy Skin Care Routine:

Cleanse, moisturize, and apply sunscreen daily to keep your skin clear and glowing.

2 Well-Groomed Eyebrows:

Regularly shape and groom your eyebrows to frame your face and enhance your natural beauty.

3 Maintain Healthy Hair:

Wash and condition your hair regularly, and keep it trimmed to maintain its health and shine.

4 Good Oral Hygiene:

Brush and floss your teeth daily, and consider whitening treatments to maintain a bright smile.

5 Clean and Trimmed Nails:

Keep your nails clean, trimmed, and optionally polished for a polished appearance.

6 Moisturized Lips:

Use lip balm to keep your lips hydrated and soft, enhancing their natural color and texture.

7 Do Gua sha/ facial massage:

Aids in lymphatic drainage, relieves tension from jaw and brow, increased blood circulation, defined face.

8 Maintain Good Posture:

Stand and sit up straight to exude confidence and grace, which enhances your overall appearance.

9 Regular Exercise:

Stay active to maintain a toned body and healthy skin, which contributes to an attractive appearance.



Follow @TheOpulentFemme for daily tips on beauty, self-improvement, and becoming your best self!

title: Collagen For Men
description:
Men's skin is generally thicker, oilier, and ages differently than women's skin.
Oiliness 
Men's skin is oilier and shinier than women's skin.
This is due to larger pores, more active sebaceous glands, and more sebum production.
Aging 
Men may age more quickly than women, with signs of aging appearing earlier.
Men are most affected by sagging skin combined with puffy eyes and dark circles.
Other differences. 
Men's skin can experience problems with sensitive skin, acne, skin aging, and blemished skin. 


Skin care
Men's care products should be tailored to their needs. 


Men can incorporate anti-aging skin care products into their daily routine. 





Men can benefit from taking collagen supplements. Collagen is the most abundant protein in the human body, and it helps maintain the health of skin, hair, bones, joints, and muscles. 
Potential benefits
Joint health: Collagen can help with joint pain, stiffness, and inflammation. 


Muscle strength: Collagen may help with muscle growth and strength, especially for men who exercise. 


Heart health: Collagen helps keep arteries healthy and may reduce the risk of heart attack and stroke. 


Skin and hair: Collagen can help prevent premature aging of skin and hair.

Its a must buy
